{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-js","path":"/module3","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"courseId":"LeapFROGS"}},"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"exercise","properties":{"id":"1","title":"Timeseries Anatomy"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This training introduces you to key concepts in timeseries analysis."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The training materials can be accessed "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://figshare.com/ndownloader/files/46749886"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Please read the presentation, as well as other helpful materials (e.g. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://figshare.com/articles/book/Data_Analysis_in_the_Earth_Environmental_Sciences/1014336"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Part 2 of this book"}]},{"type":"text","value":"), then answer the following questions:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Questions"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Do all timeseries need to be evenly-spaced?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"choice","properties":{"id":"03-01"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"opt","properties":{"text":"No",",":"","correct":"true"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\nMany timeseries, particularly in the geosciences, are unevenly spaced. However, even spacing is assumed by many methods, so care must be taken.\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"opt","properties":{"text":"Yes"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\nIt is true that many methods _assume_ even spacing, but that is by no means a requirement. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If your analysis requires even spacing, what should you do (multiple answers possible):"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"choice","properties":{"id":"03-02"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"opt","properties":{"text":"Interpolation",",":"","correct":"true"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\nNon-replicability of results doesn't mean that something is wrong. In fact, science advancement relies on getting more information with different data/methods and obtaining inconsistent answers.\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"opt","properties":{"text":"Binning",",":"","correct":"true"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\nBinning in coarser, even intervals is another possible option\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"opt","properties":{"text":"Gaussian kernel",",":"","correct":"true"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\nBinning in coarser, even intervals with some Gaussian smoothing is another possible options\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"opt","properties":{"text":"Change analysis methods"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\nThat is always available to you, but it is an extreme step. For one thing, there may not be an easily accessible, alternative method for what you are trying to do. And getting to even spacing might be less painful than you think (see options above)\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For practical exercises in Python go "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http